The paper presents a new algorithm that integrates approximative models and intelligent sampling of the objective function to minimize the number of evaluations required by MAP-Elites. This algorithm is applied to a 2D airfoil design problem, which involves exploring a design space to find high-performing solutions that vary according to user-defined features. This problem is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), robotics (cs.RO), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
